## 3. Results

### 3.1 Model Performance on B3DB Test Set

| Model | AUC-ROC | AUC-PR | Accuracy | F1 | Brier Score |
|-------|---------|--------|----------|----|-------------|
| Random Forest (calibrated) | **0.9617** | **0.9757** | **0.884** | **0.912** | **0.082** |
| Logistic Regression (calibrated) | 0.9109 | 0.9345 | 0.862 | 0.890 | 0.128 |
| GNN AttentiveFP (Colab GPU) | 0.910 | — | — | — | — |
| DeepChem RF baseline | 0.868 | — | — | — | — |

The calibrated Random Forest achieved AUC-ROC of 0.9617, representing a 9.2%
improvement over the published DeepChem Random Forest baseline (AUC-ROC 0.868).
The Brier score of 0.082 indicates well-calibrated probability estimates; a Brier
score of 0.25 would correspond to a random classifier, and a score below 0.10 is
generally considered well-calibrated for imbalanced classification tasks.

### 3.2 Benchmark Validation on 15 Curated Molecules

To evaluate the complete decision system beyond aggregate metrics, the model was
validated on 15 molecules with unambiguous experimentally established BBB status.

| Compound | Expected | Predicted | Score | CNS | Correct |
|----------|----------|-----------|-------|-----|---------|
| Caffeine | BBB+ | BBB+ | 0.837 | 5/6 | Yes |
| Diazepam | BBB+ | BBB+ | 0.928 | 6/6 | Yes |
| Nicotine | BBB+ | BBB+ | 0.928 | 6/6 | Yes |
| Fluoxetine | BBB+ | BBB+ | 0.928 | 6/6 | Yes |
| Morphine | BBB+ | BBB+ | 0.928 | 6/6 | Yes |
| Atropine | BBB+ | BBB+ | 0.846 | 6/6 | Yes |
| Dopamine | Borderline | Borderline | 0.697 | 6/6 | Yes |
| Serotonin | Borderline | Borderline | 0.691 | 6/6 | Yes |
| L-DOPA | Borderline | Borderline | 0.466 | 4/6 | Yes |
| Gabapentin | Borderline | Borderline | 0.727 | 6/6 | Yes |
